{"name": "liteindex", "metadata": {"name": "liteindex", "version": "0.0.3.3", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Programming Language :: Python", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.6", "Programming Language :: Python :: Implementation :: CPython"], "home_page": "https://github.com/notAI-tech/liteindex", "license": "MIT", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "SQLite based queryable python indexes for dicts and lists", "upload_time": 1733805043}, "documentation": ["\n# LiteIndex\nEmbedded, thread and process safe, disk backed, easy to use, query-able, fast Index (Cache) implementations\n\n```python\npip install --upgrade liteindex[all]\n```\n\n### DefinedIndex\n- [Documentation](https://github.com/notAI-tech/LiteIndex/blob/main/DefinedIndex.md) | [Detailed example](https://github.com/notAI-tech/LiteIndex/blob/main/examples/defined_index_example.py) | [Benchmarks](https://github.com/notAI-tech/LiteIndex/tree/main/benchmarks/DefinedIndex)\n- fixed schema index i.e: schema has to be defined before hand\n- `number`, `boolean`, `datetime`, `string`, `compressed_string`, `blob`, `json`, `normalized_embedding`, and `other` types are supported and `can be queried upon`\n- can store any python objects with varying levels of query-ability\n- `Query language is subset of mongodb's`. All queries are documented\n- seamless, very fast nearest neighbor search with filtering. can order by, filter by as usual with embeddings\n- works across threads, processes seamlessly\n- handy features like search and update in single query, batch operation support for update, search, del, pop etc ..\n- in-place math operations support wherever applicable i.e: += etc can be done in single query optimally\n- compression is supported natively and optional custom compression dictionaries can be built automatically\n\n### KVIndex\n- [Documentation](https://github.com/notAI-tech/LiteIndex/blob/main/KVIndex.md) | [Detailed example](https://github.com/notAI-tech/LiteIndex/blob/main/examples/defined_index_example.py) | [Benchmarks](https://github.com/notAI-tech/LiteIndex/tree/main/benchmarks/DefinedIndex)\n- simple key value store, can store any python objects, can be queried for equality, sorting, max, min etc wherever applicable\n- in-place math operations support wherever applicable i.e: += etc can be done in single query optimally\n- has a python dict like interface\n- batch operation support for update, search, del, pop etc ..\n- ultra fast, works across threads, processes seamlessly\n- Eviction policies supported: `LRU`, `LFU`, `any` and age based invalidation and size, count based eviction\n\n### function_cache\n- [Documentation](https://github.com/notAI-tech/LiteIndex/blob/main/function_cache.md) | [Detailed example](https://github.com/notAI-tech/LiteIndex/blob/main/examples/function_cache_example.py) | [Benchmarks](https://github.com/notAI-tech/LiteIndex/tree/main/benchmarks/function_cache)\n- based on KVIndex, can be used to cache function calls of any type\n- batch inference caching friendly\n"], "modules": [{"name": "liteindex", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "liteindex.DefinedIndex", "xref": {"fqname": "liteindex.defined_index.DefinedIndex", "project": null}}, {"name": "liteindex.DefinedTypes", "xref": {"fqname": "liteindex.defined_serializers.DefinedTypes", "project": null}}, {"name": "liteindex.EvictionCfg", "xref": {"fqname": "liteindex.common_utils.EvictionCfg", "project": null}}, {"name": "liteindex.function_cache", "xref": {"fqname": "liteindex.function_cache.function_cache", "project": null}}, {"name": "liteindex.get_defined_index_names_in_db", "xref": {"fqname": "liteindex.defined_index.get_defined_index_names_in_db", "project": null}}, {"name": "liteindex.KVIndex", "xref": {"fqname": "liteindex.kv_index.KVIndex", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "liteindex.defined_serializers", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "liteindex.defined_serializers.hash_bytes", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "data", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "liteindex.defined_serializers.serialize_record", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "schema", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "record", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "compressor", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "_id", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "_updated_at", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "liteindex.defined_serializers.deserialize_record", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "schema", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "record", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "decompressor", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [{"name": "liteindex.defined_serializers.np", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "liteindex.defined_serializers.schema_property_to_column_type", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "liteindex.defined_serializers.DefinedTypes", "bases": [], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "liteindex.defined_serializers.DefinedTypes.number", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "liteindex.defined_serializers.DefinedTypes.string", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "liteindex.defined_serializers.DefinedTypes.boolean", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "liteindex.defined_serializers.DefinedTypes.datetime", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "liteindex.defined_serializers.DefinedTypes.compressed_string", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "liteindex.defined_serializers.DefinedTypes.blob", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "liteindex.defined_serializers.DefinedTypes.other", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "liteindex.defined_serializers.DefinedTypes.json", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "liteindex.defined_serializers.DefinedTypes.normalized_embedding", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": []}, {"name": "liteindex.function_cache", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "liteindex.function_cache.function_cache", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "func", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "path", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "ram_cache_mb", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "eviction_policy", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "max_number_of_items", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "max_size_in_mb", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "invalidate_after_seconds", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "liteindex.kv_index_utils", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "liteindex.kv_index_utils.create_tables", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "store_key", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "preserve_order", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "eviction", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "conn", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["store_key=True: This adds an additional 'pickled_key' BLOB column to store serialized keys.", "TABLE kv_index: key_hash BLOB, num_value NUMBER, string_value TEXT, pickled_value BLOB, pickled_key BLOB, PRIMARY KEY (key_hash)", "store_key=False: Without 'store_key', the 'pickled_key' column is not created.", "TABLE kv_index: key_hash BLOB, num_value NUMBER, string_value TEXT, pickled_value BLOB, PRIMARY KEY (key_hash)", "preserve_order=True or eviction.invalidate_after_seconds > 0: Adds an 'updated_at' INTEGER column for storing timestamps to maintain order or handle time-based eviction.", "TABLE kv_index with 'updated_at': key_hash BLOB, ..., updated_at INTEGER, PRIMARY KEY (key_hash)", "eviction.policy=EvictLRU (Least Recently Used): Includes a 'last_accessed_time' INTEGER column to track access time for LRU eviction policy.", "TABLE kv_index with LRU: key_hash BLOB, ..., last_accessed_time INTEGER, PRIMARY KEY (key_hash)", "INDEX kv_index_last_accessed_time_idx ON kv_index(last_accessed_time) for efficient LRU eviction querying.", "eviction.policy=EvictLFU (Least Frequently Used): Includes an 'access_frequency' INTEGER column to track access count for LFU eviction policy.", "TABLE kv_index with LFU: key_hash BLOB, ..., access_frequency INTEGER, PRIMARY KEY (key_hash)", "INDEX kv_index_access_frequency_idx ON kv_index(access_frequency) for efficient LFU eviction querying.", "eviction.max_size_in_mb is set: An additional 'size_in_bytes' INTEGER column is added to track the size of each stored item in bytes.", "TABLE kv_index with size tracking: key_hash BLOB, ..., size_in_bytes INTEGER, PRIMARY KEY (key_hash)", "The function also creates a 'kv_index_num_metadata' table to store numeric metadata about the key-value index.", "TABLE kv_index_num_metadata: key TEXT PRIMARY KEY, num INTEGER", "This metadata table includes entries for current size (in MB), flags for store_key and preserve_order, eviction policies and their parameters like max size, max number of items, and invalidation period.", "An additional index is created for the 'updated_at' column if `preserve_order=True` or `eviction.invalidate_after_seconds > 0` to enable efficient querying by update time.", "INDEX kv_index_updated_at_idx ON kv_index(updated_at)"]}, {"name": "liteindex.kv_index_utils.__get_column_name", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "value", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "liteindex.kv_index_utils.create_where_clause", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "query", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [{"name": "liteindex.kv_index_utils.__policy_to_number_int_id", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "lit